SUMMARY:Michael Brunström: William Tell versus the Algorithm
LOCATION:Camden Comedy Club\, 100 Camden High Street\, London
DESCRIPTION:Medieval Swiss folklore meets AI in this silly and surreal new 
 caper from the incomparable Michael Brunström. **** "A joy" (Scotsman) Lik
 e Robin Hood\, William Tell is a folk hero who symbolises defiance in the f
 ace of oppression. Most famous for shooting an apple off his son's head wit
 h a crossbow\, he'll use it again to attack the AI algorithms that are desi
 gned to disempower\, divide and distract us. Join his cry of "Death to the 
 algorithm! Down with tyrants! Freedom for Switzerland!" **** "An artistic g
 enius" (Skinny) **** "You will see nothing else that is so clever and funny
 " (North West End) Michael Brunström is a surrealist comedian based in Lon
 don. His previous shows have covered topics as diverse as steam trains\, Jo
 hn Constable's 'The Hay Wain'\, parsley\, the Great Fire of London and moth
 s. He is a winner of the Malcolm Hardee Award for Comic Originality. His 20
 24 show 'Copernicus Now' was nominated for the Best Show Award at the Leice
 ster Comedy Festival.\nMore info: https://comedyatlas.app/comedy-atlas/even
 t/michael-brunstrom-william-tell-versus-the-algorithm/
URL:https://comedyatlas.app/comedy-atlas/event/michael-brunstrom-william-te
 ll-versus-the-algorithm/
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
